result.execSummary:
The defendant Stanley W. Stubbe Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: Defendant and Attorney Szilagyi appear via video from the WC Jail.

RETURN ON WARRANT: Case called @ 1:04 p.m. Defendant Stanley W. Stubbe in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will not be represented by SPD if released from custody. ADA Anderson requesting a small cash bond. Atty Szilagyi requesting a signature bond. Court orders $500 Sig Bond.  STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint. Defendant wishes to resolve the matter today.   Defendant waives his right to be personally present in the courtroom.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Guilty.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Statement by the defendant. Court orders: 4 days WC Jail - 3 days CFTS - Time served sentence, Costs w/ 60 DTP or PP. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights faxed to the jail.

Case Called @ 3:44 PM: Defendant Stanley W. Stubbe not in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In light of nonappearance, Arrest Warrant Authorized with Statewide Extradition.    Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.
